    <text>
        <body>
            <div style="handwritten" type="letter">
                <head type="title">King Ferdinand I to Pál Várday and Miklós Oláh (Wiener Neustadt,
                    18 September 1548)</head>
                <floatingText type="regesta">
                    <body>
                        <p>He is attaching István Losonczy’s supplicatio, from which he will
                            understand Losonczy’s complaint and why he resents a servitor called
                            Jakab. Since this Jakab really may have hurt him, he charges Oláh with
                            investigating the matter, and having heard both of them, he should make
                            a just decision so neither of them can complain later. </p>
                    </body>
                </floatingText>
                <pb/>
                <p>Ferdinandus etc. Reverendissime in Christo Frater ac Venerabiles Devoti
                    Fideles nobis Dilecti!</p>
                <p>Ex supplici libello<note type="critic">We do not know this
                        document.</note> magnifici fidelis nobis dilecti <persName>Stephani de
                        Lossuntz</persName><note type="critic">István Losonczy (†1552) was loyal to
                        King John I, then changed sides and remained loyal to King Ferdinand I. In
                        1547, he became <hi rend="italic">ispán</hi> of Nógrád county. From 1551, he
                        was <hi rend="italic">ispán</hi> of Temes county and participated in the
                        Transylvanian campaign, see <hi rend="smallcap">Kenyeres</hi> 1982, 89.
                        Sebestyén Tinódi Lantos’ lay commemorates his heroic death: <hi
                            rend="italic">A vég Temes­várban Losonczi István haláláról</hi>.</note>
                    comitis comitatus Neugradiensis hisce litteris nostris incluso <del
                        corresp="scriba">intelligetis</del><add corresp="scriba" type="insert"
                        >intelliget</add>
                    <add corresp="scriba" type="insert">Fidelitas Vestra</add> querelas ac gravamina
                    sua contra et adversus quendam <persName>Iacobum</persName><note type="critic"
                        >We do not know him more closely.</note> nuncupatum litteratum servitorem
                    suum. Quoniam vero ipse quoque <persName>Iacobus</persName> posset praetendere
                    aliquid iuris contra dicti <persName>Lossunzi</persName>, idcirco mandamus
                    Fidelitati Vestrae, quod summa cum diligentia utriusque partis querelas ac
                    gravamina audiatis ac perpendatis, et super illis plane statuat decernatque,
                    quod aequum et iustum fuerit, <del corresp="scriba">In qua sane fidelitas</del>
                    ita ut neutri parti ulla sit amplius <add corresp="scriba" type="insert"
                        >iusta</add> conquerendi causa. In quo sane Fidelitas Vestra exsequetur
                    voluntatem nostram.</p>
                <p>Datum in <placeName>Nova Civitate</placeName> 18. Septembris 1548.</p>
            </div>
            <div style="handwritten" type="verso">
                <head>Probably on the outer side:</head>
                <p>Strigoniensi et Zagrabiensi.</p>
            </div>
